    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/186</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-11T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 12, 6.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7923. The following for <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_JTD1"
                        >Jones</persName>, War Trade Board, from <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName>:</p>
                <p>Dutch offer to unload ships in New York, 100,000 tons gross, to be permanently
                    placed at disposal of Belgian Relief, <hi rend="italic">Zeelandia</hi> to be
                    allowed to proceed home, eight boats from colonies be allowed to go to Holland
                    and return cargoes to count in our rations. Ships named <hi rend="italic"
                        >Celebes, Ceylon, Nias, Ternate, Gorontalo, Adonis, Hercules</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Samarinda</hi>, 66,000 tons cargo capacity <hi rend="italic"
                        >in toto</hi>. All other ships in United States to be sent for one trip as
                    we designate out of present submarine zone, not all on long trips as to Java and
                    Australia British ore. Considering Relief looks good to me and would produce
                    good effect in Holland.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
